  "text": "So we are forced to a simpler scheme, similar to that described by [CITATION_1] and often used for stiff systems. The idea is to alternate integration steps of the fast nodes and the slow edges. When integrating nodes, the edge states are held fixed and node states updated by accumulating incoming spikes and (leakily) integrating them using equation (11). When integrating edges, the node states are held fixed and the edge states updated using a forward Euler approximation of equation (6). This is simple to implement and greatly speeds up the simulation, at the cost of some loss of accuracy.",
